AGI - "His mouth smells like tyranny." The Russian journalist Vladimir Soloviev is speaking so, live TV, to the vice president of the European Parliament, Pina Picierno, after the stop to the episode of the program 'The state of things' that had as guests the Russian anchorman friend of Vladimir Putin. To unleash the ires of the Russian journalist was in particular the post in which Picierno asked to stop the program conducted by Massimo Giletti. >
"Giletti announces that he will host in his broadcast on Rai 3 Soloviev, which is a Russian propagandist hit by Ue sanctions - says the Russian journalist reading the post of Picierno -. I ask the network manager and the Supervisory Board to intervene to prevent it. The Italian public service cannot be megaphones for Russian disinformation."
