Hence the words written by Picierno, to which Soloviev responds with a very hard attack conferred by a gestuality infarction of anti Italian clichè»: "That's what you need to understand miserable pious beast: that you go against all the principles of European democracy," continues the journalist in his monologue in the studio of Rossija 1. And then, in Italian: "But go, licensed idiot." And again, in Russian: "If you dare, you filthy beast, accuse me of misinformation, then what would you say about Donald Trump who claims that you European sieti of liars? What do you say to the cyber king Sachs who claims that your Russianphobia is &nbsp;'pazzesca' (in Italian, ndr.)? Are you crazy? Shame of the human race", again in Italian, "here you are. And note: they are introduced in the affairs of Italian journalism, but they are afraid to enter the Romanian elections." &nbsp;
"Solidarity to Vice-President Pina&nbsp;Picierno, target of unacceptable attacks. The European Parliament strongly supports democracy and freedom of expression, and opposes all forms of hate incitement." The European Parliament writes it on X. E&nbsp; strong solidarity was expressed, always on X, by the head of the PD delegation to the European Parliament, Nicola Zingaretti "against the shameful ennesim attacks coming from Russia. A sequel of serious, vulgar and unacceptable insults that will not cast in all of us the determination to continue to tell the truth".
